Basic Usage

    $(document).ready(function()
	{
		new Radiator('http://localhost:8080/job/FooBar%20Project/', '#project_status1', '#culprits_info_1', '1.mp3', 2000).init();
		new Radiator('http://localhost:8080/job/SecondBazProject/', '#project_status2', '#culprits_info_2', '1.mp3', 2000).init();
	});

Add as many Radiator objects as you like.
The signature parameters for a Radiator object are:

    new Radiator([url], [status_text_div_id], [culprit_data_div_id], [failure_sound_file], [refresh_delay]).init();i

Support for rescheduling status update after a network error from a GET request is now available.
